# Privacy Policy ‚Äì Reporeply

Last updated: January 2026

Reporeply respects user privacy and follows the principle of least privilege.

---

## 1. Information We Access

Reporeply accesses only the data required to function:

- Repository metadata
- Issue titles, bodies, authors, labels, and timestamps
- Installation and event metadata from GitHub webhooks

---

## 2. Information We Do NOT Collect

Reporeply does **not** collect or store:

- Personal profile data
- Email addresses
- Passwords or credentials
- Source code
- Pull request data
- Private messages

---

## 3. Data Storage

- Reporeply does **not** maintain a persistent database
- All processing is done in memory
- No issue content is stored after processing

---

## 4. Authentication & Security

- Uses GitHub App authentication
- Uses short-lived installation access tokens
- Webhooks are verified using a shared secret
- Cron endpoints are protected by a secret header

---

## 5. Third Parties

Reporeply does not share data with any third parties.  
All interactions occur directly between GitHub and the deployed Reporeply instance.

---

## 6. User Control

Users can:
- Uninstall the GitHub App at any time
- Remove repository access instantly
- Disable functionality by uninstalling

Once uninstalled, Reporeply no longer receives any data.

---

## 7. Changes to This Policy

If this policy changes, updates will be published in this repository.

---

## 8. Contact

For privacy-related questions, please open an issue in the repository.
